This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image representation and feature fusion. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new method to improve the performance of a neural network. Additionally, it could be categorized under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories as it involves the use of convolutional neural networks and image datasets.
